'''Child Marriage in Mauritania'''. In 2017 in [[Mauritania]], 37% of girls are married off before the 18 years old. 14% are married before they turn 15.<ref name="girlsnotbrides.org">{{cite|url=https://www.girlsnotbrides.org/child-marriage/mauritania/|title=Child marriage around the world: MAURITANIA|work=[[Girls Not Brides]]}}</ref> Mauritania is the 19th highest nation in the world for child marriage.
A third of women in Mauritania marry early.<ref name="worldbank">{{cite|url=https://openknowledge.worldbank.org/bitstream/handle/10986/24551/Basic0profile00rriage0in0Mauritania.pdf?sequence=1&isAllowed=y|title=BASIC PROFILE OF CHILD MARRIAGE IN MAURITANIA|format=PDF|date=March 2016|author1=Chata Malé|author2=Quentin Wodon|publisher=[[World Bank Group]]}}</ref>
